    <readme><![CDATA[Allows content administrators to maintain properties for content nodes without having access to the Document Type tree in the Settings section.

Usage & Configurtion:  

parentNodeId: This is the Node id of the root Dynamic Property Folder node of your properties tree in the content section.

Folder DocumentType Alias: This is the Alias of the document type that you are using to be your properties container.  By default the package installs with a folder alias of dynamicPropertyFolder

Property DocumentType Alias: This is the alias of the document type that you are using to be your property.  By default the package installs with a property alias of dynamicProperty.  For validation to work you must have a property on your document type of type Yes/No with an alias of Mandatory.

Validation: For validation to work your property document type must have a property of type Yes/No and have an alias of  mandatory.  For validation to work the Dynamic Properties Datatype Property on your Document Type must be set to Mandatory.

]]></readme>
